       fhir:comment [ fhir:v "The individual does not speak the default language of the organization, and hence requires an interpreter. If other languages are in the Communications list, then that would be the type of interpreter required.\r\r*While this extension is named patient-interpreterRequired for backwards compatibility, it may also be used on RelatedPerson, Practitioner, Encounter, Appointment and ServiceRequest.*\r\rWhen used on Patient, RelatedPerson, or Practitioner, it indicates a default or assumed need for an interpreter.\rWhen used on Encounter, Appointment or ServiceRequest, it indicates that an interpreter is needed to facilitate communication between some participants in the service.\rThe encounter-level evaluation of whether an interpreter is needed might involve evaluating the language proficiencies of the participants." ] ;
